Rally toho me! Hehehelp me escape, gah, please! Heh, urgh...

You see an adventure who has let her avarice get the better of her  shes thrown open a chest in search of loot, only to find a tentacle tickle trap in the chest! The ash-haired woman must have some superhuman reflexes, as she was very close to avoiding the trap  she must have turned and leapt as soon as she opened it and saw there was a nasty surprise waiting for her. The tentacles in the chest are at full extension, but theyve only been able to snare her ankles and nothing more. It seems to be a stalemate, as the tentacles tug and the ashen-haired girl grunts and holds onto the ground, her fingers grabbing onto a tree for leverage.
Whats that adventurer thinking, opening every chest she sees? What a silly goose.
You say that as if we havent done that dozens of times.
Looks like you could use a hand, huh?

You hear a rip as the tentacles tear off the leather soles of the female adventurers boots. Seconds later, her arms shake and angry titters fly from her pursed lips as the tentacles introduce themselves to her bare soles. From the way her fingers are trembling for purchase, the tickling must be quite intense (or her feet very sensitive  or perhaps both).
Urgh, yes! Huhuhuhurry! Grahahaha! Why dididihid it have to be tickling! My trahahahining never prepared me for thihihihihis! What kind of monster ch-ch-ch-chest is thihihihis?
Ah, you like my chest, do you? Works wonders on nosy adventurers such as yourself.

In a valiant attempt, the ashen-haired girl goes for the sword on her back, but Matilda ducks, and after the sword goes whizzing over her head. Giggling, Matilda slips her fingers in the armpit while she has a chance, and the adventurer shrieks with laughter. The chest swallows the girl up to her thighs, and from the sound of her anguished laughter, the things it's doing to her toes, feet, knees, and thighs cant be anything good. If that werent bad enough, Matilda sits on the girls back and digs her nails into both armpits at once.
Oooh, shes really rumbling under me! Guess shes one of those super defiant ticklish types, huh?
The adventurer tries to reach back to jab backwards with her sword, but Matilda reaches out and snaps the blade in half as easily if it were a twig.
None of that now, just focus on breathing and laughing, hehehehe... but I tell you what, Ill stop tickling you if you can tell me a joke.
Im no jehehester to ehehentertain you!

Is that so? Hmmm, are your toes ticklish, I wonder? I spied a bit of black nail varnish on them, so I take it you pamper them a fair bit? Lets send a few tentacles to explore under and between them and see what we find...
Oh, the toes are ticklish? Ah, as I hoped! Lets keep this up till we get a good joke from you, yes? Or maybe you want to keep going? Who am I to understand human inclinations...

The chest gulps another few inches of the ticklish adventurer, claiming her waist as well. From the way her green eyes flicker and the angry moan of laughter, the tentacles have taken to exploring this new spot with cruel curiosity. You imagine theyre doing all sorts of deviously diabolical things to her womanhood to make her gasp and groan like that.
Matilda turns you to with an amused shrug.
She says stop, but she doesnt say a joke to make me stop. Guess she needs some time to think of one. Ill come back later.
With a final parting poke in the ribs, the Tickle Lord flies away, leaving the ashen-haired adventurer to curse and splutter with more despondent laughter.
Um, need some help thinking of a joke?
I'm not plahahaying along for thahahat wretch!
Up to you, I guess. Enjoy the tickles.

The sight of the silvery blue marble serpent tickling the Chronicler fills you with questions. Where did this creature come from? Was it sculpted by the Tickle Lords magic? Was the marble already here, or was it brought here for some nefarious purpose? You suppose the moored ship beside the shore may provide some answers, but youve already kinda lost interest. The peril of the squealing blonde Chronicler is far more immediate and relevant.
You thehehere! Can you plehehehease hehehelp!?

You consider asking her questions about the origins of the marble, but you decide to hold off for now. The pretty Chronicler is on the ground, with her ankles locked in the jaws of the marble serpent statue. The two other serpents seem to be licking her feet with tongues of pale marble, and although they leave now saliva behind, you can see the woman gasping and groaning with very flick. The Chronicler seems to read your expression and answers your unasked question, flushing.
Thehehe marble is reheheally cold! It feels sohoho tingly, ahahaha!

You watch the precious metal glint in the dim light. As thin and flexible as any true snake, the tongues dance upon every curve and crevice of the Chroniclers long milky soles. You watch for a while, quirking a knowing eyebrow as the Chroniclers feet splay while she moans with laughter. Those tongues really are something. You watch as those pale tongues flick and caress the centres of the pale soles before moving up to lap and swipe at the long, unpainted toes. Its no wonder the Chronicler is a heaving, chortling mess with three of those tongues slinking and stroking across her soles.
Erm, those snake things look pretty tough, and Id rather not fight them. Think you can answer our questions while theyre tickling you?
Whahahahat? Youre suhuhupposed to be heheroes! Hehehelp me first! Help my pooohohoor feet!
Uh, were not adventurers and were not heroes. Were also kinda weak.
I dohoho not wish to hear your ehehexcuses! Hehelp me get a breheheak or Im not telling you ahahanything!
You know if you give us the information, itll help us beat the Tickle Lords and theoretically free you more quickly, right? Wheres your sense of duty as a Chronicler?
The blonde Chronicler bursts out a roar of laughter as two of the marble serpents tongues start snaking through her toes.
Nohohoho, nohohot my tohohohoes! Grrrahaha, Im sehehehelfish, ohohokay? You dont hehelp me, I dont hehelp you, and thats fihihinal, hahahahaha!
My, how stubborn. Guess we better find a way then. Ideas, sister?
Well, the easiest thing would be to find a bomb or something to blow up those statues.
Yeah, that would be easy. But lets say we didnt have anything like that and just had to make do with the garbage lying around.
Hmm, maybe we could find a rag or something to wrap around her feet? Then shed at least get a breather while they figured out how to rip them off.
I dont know, sis. I mean, they figured out how to take her shoes and socks off easily enough.
Thahahat was my ohohohown fahahahault! I took my sh-sh-shoes off and was rehehehesting with my feeheet in the water, gahahahaha!
Well, that wasnt very smart when dealing with a land ruled by Tickle Lords, was it? Anyway, sit tight. We'll do what we can. Just keep your word!
Hmm, maybe we could find a rag or something to wrap around her feet? Then shed at least get a breather while they figured out how to rip them off.
Hmm, maybe we could find a rag or something to wrap around her feet? Then shed at least get a breather while they figured out how to rip them off.

You drape the heavy black cloak over the Chronicler's bare feet, winding and knotting it several times. Two of the serpents keep on 'licking' away, but the third seems perplexed, poking and trying to dislodge the dark cloth. You have some time to talk now, but you're not sure how much.
The Chronicler gulps in air, still twitching a little as the serpent statues paw at her feet.
Alright, ask your questions. And thank you...
Grey-skinned, dark haired, and notoriously without mercy. He possess some kind of sorcery that animates statues, turns them into his slaves. He's a menace, and I'd avoid him at all costs.

Hard to comprehend her. I've seen her traps ensnare a few of the knights I was assigned too, but after tormenting them a while, she'd let them go. I don't understand what she's trying to do. Maybe she's toying with us? Or maybe she secretly wants us to overthrow her and Brock? I don't know.
Free the adventurers? If we could mass up and fight the Tickle Lords, we might have a chance...
How'd that go for you last time?
Very poorly. We got lost in the ruins, stumbled into traps, or picked off.
Or in your case, voluntarily took off her shoes and got tickled silly for it.
No need to bring that up! Anyway, if you can't free the others, perhaps you could try to drive a wedge between the Tickle Lords? I don't know, but they seem to have a complicated relationship.
Hmmmm, that's not a terrible idea...

No clue, I'm afraid. Matilda can fly and whizz around, but at least Brock tends to be easier to anticipate with those big heavy footsteps of his. But he already seems to know what's going on. I think his statues are his informants...
Alright, thats enough from you two. Matilda may insist on ignoring the very real threat that you are, but Im not tolerating it any longer.
Oh, Brock, hey! I was about to deal with those two!
Is that so? My statues hear everything in these ruins, and what they heard is a dereliction of duty.
Brock, you know it turns me on when you use fancy words, but could you speak plainly please?
Get out of my way. Youre not dealing with them, so I am. Now.
Think we'd best beat a hasty retreat, bro.

The end of the Chronicler's sentence is punctuated by a ripping sound and a squeal, as the serpents tear apart the rag that had shrouded and protected her sensitive bare feet. The tongues flick and stroke over them deftly and swiftly, even faster than before as if making up for lost time, and the pretty blonde young woman is quickly tickled back into hysterics as the tongue carve across all the familiarly devastating hot spots across her feet.
Don't think there's much we can do for you now. Sorry!
Welcome all! Please make yourself at home <3
A Chronicler! Got a pretty obvious question for you that we hope you can answer -- what exactly is going on with the two Tickle Lords here?
Hehehehe, hehehelp me down fihihihirst! Plehehease, hahahandsome!

Unfortunately, there isn't really a ton that you can do. The Chronicler is bound tightly to the stone slab ornament, with rocky hands emerging from the sides of it to prod her sides and grab her ribs. Further hands lift up her ankles so another set of hands can scrabble across her pale soles, which you can help but notice are unusually pretty for a Chronicler, with a silver anklet, pink nail varnish, and even a toe-ring on one foot. It's really quite strange considering your impression of the profession of Chroniclers is basically a notch above working-class.
I don't think we can help you, sorry. We don't have any sledgehammers on us. Say, why have you got such fancy feet? Not what I expected from a Chronicler, not that I'm complaining.
She was probably trying to bag herself a husband or paramour among the adventurers here. Look at those curls... I know the type.
Guhuhuhuh, I am nohohohot gohohonna talk about mehehehee!
Yeah, that's a yes. But let's move on.
Nohoho! I'm nohohot gonna talk to you if you're gohohohonna be mehehean to me, hahaha!
You reach out and goose her ribs. Cissy chuckles and goes along, raking her long nails over the Chronicler's insteps.
Wahahahahaha! Alright, stop, stop, stahahahap! It's alreheheheady bahahad enohohough!

You and Cissy stop tickling, though the stone hands continue digging and scrabbling across her spots. The pretty Chronicler pants and gulps down air as best as she can from this reduced tickling, though it's still pretty intense.
Alright, give us some info so we can help you, okay? We wanna know how to defeat the Tickle Lords here. Have you encountered them?
Tickle Lord! Kihihinda handsome in a ruhuhugged kinda way! Grey skin! Controls the statues! He dihihihid this toohoho mehehe!
The Chronicler gestures downwards to her tickle-ravaged body, but it's hardly necessary. You get the picture.
Rehehed hair! A pihihihixie, I thihink! She mahahade many trahahaps around here!
We know to be careful, thanks.
I think she reheheheally fancied hihihim! But he just wahahasn't that intohohoho heheheher!
We kinda got that impression too. Ah, the pangs of unrequited love. Wonder how we can use that to our advantage.
I think the bihihig guy is somewhere to the north, ahahaha! No idea for the gihihihirl!
Alright, thats enough from you two. Matilda may insist on ignoring the very real threat that you are, but Im not tolerating it any longer.
Oh, Brock, hey! I was about to deal with those two!
Is that so? My statues hear everything in these ruins, and what they heard is a dereliction of duty.
Brock, you know it turns me on when you use fancy words, but could you speak plainly please?
Get out of my way. Youre not dealing with them, so I am. Now.
Think we'd best beat a hasty retreat, bro.
Thanks, pretty thing. We'll do what we can to get you out.
Thanks, pretty thing. We'll do what we can to get you out.

Inside the chest, you find a stuffed animal. From how worn and faded the colours are, you surmise its quite old indeed. You dont really want to log around a big teddy bear, so you just stuff it back inside.
Oooh, a chest! But there's nothing in here, not even a trap... lame.

You reach you hand in and slowly pull out a small worn book from the chest. You flip open the book and see its a diary written in a youthful scrawl. Its probably Tickle Lord Matildas? You look at the latest entry.

Brock gave me flowers yesterday. Well, not truly flowers  they were herbs he found from the ground. He said I should eat them for a healthier diet and not just relying on mirth and lust energy. Isnt he sweet?
Oooh, a chest! But there's nothing in here, not even a trap... lame.
I'm guessing one of the other adventurers already deactivated this one.

Looks like quite the battle! The female knight in the thick plate armour wields a sharp sabre, her weapon deflecting and parrying the stone blades from the three statues attacking her. Its an impressive contest, as the three stone swords fall in concert as the warrior ducks, blocks, and counterattacks, but you quickly realise its a battle the lone warrior is doomed to lose. Her counter-slashes leaves tiny nicks in the stone that do little more than dull her weapon, and shes panting and sweaty from the effort of defending against three attackers. Meanwhile, the stone statues are as implacable and relentless as ever, their swords rising and falling again.
The weight of my sword is the weight of my pride... I shant lose!

Unfortunately, moments after this, the prideful adventurers weapon is knocked from her hand! She dives to retrieve it, but its too late. The middle statue lunges and grabs the swordswoman by the midsection and hauls her up.

The statues ignore her calls as they sheathe their swords, the scrapping, grating sound filling the air. The middle statue gets a firmer grip on the adventurer, lifting her up in the air by her arms as the other two statues rip away the armour with an inhuman strength.
No, I know what youre going to do, but it shant work! Im not tihihicklish!

Sure enough, the statues stone fingers squeezing around her sides, poking her ribs, and brushing her armpits lead to instant results. The statues fingers are large and ungainly, and they also dont exactly have nails, but they do a decent enough job with goosing and digging motions.
One of the statues booms with a surprisingly deep voice, a male voice, which is odd given how the statue looks like female swordswoman. You recognise the voice  its Brock, the Tickle Lord.
Ive got you now, human. And unlike my foolhardy colleague, theres no escape. Now relinquish your laughter and submit!
The knight shakes her head as the stone hands continues squeezing and poking at her, which causes low, boyish cackles to come out in starts and spurts.
I wohohohont mahahake this easy for you!
Is that so? Statues, restrain her more firmly then, and tickle her more forcefully.

There is that awful stone-scrapping sound again as the statues draw their swords again. But they dont use them as weapons. They force the knight down and lay the heavy stones atop her ankles and limbs. You can see the knight squirming to slip free or shove the stones aside, but big blocks of stone are as big as pillars, and she cant do so. The statues then rip away the last vestiges of protection  her grieves and heavy boots, and tickle her flushed bare feet in addition to her armpits.
Ahahahaha, hehehehelp! This cahahant be happening to me, hahahahah!
Not much we can do aside from spectate, right? Itll take a wrecking ball to stop those statues. Come on, lets go.
I think we don't want to get caught by those statues... let's go another way.
Ah, the two village champions, we meet again! Its been too long.
What were their names again? Damn, Ive forgotten.
Hohohow cohohould you, Cissy! We grehehew up togehehehether! Im Arthur!
I vihihihisted your fahaharm all the time! Its me, Mohohohorgan!
I guess that part of childhood must have passed me by. How are you two doing?

You suppose thats true. Both of the village champions have been captured and lifted high in the air by spooky skull statues. The spooky skull statue by the swordsman, Arthur, has a number of cracks and dents in it. Both statues are using thick stone tendrils as thick as your arms to hold the heroes up in the air, while smaller stone tendrils jab and poke their vulnerable spots. Youre reminded of some great stone octopus toying with its prey. Most of the great grey tentacles do the standard tickling stuff, dipping into armpits, poking sides, but quite a few of them are rather naughty, especially the leering skull teasing Morgan. You see a few tentacles nudging around her small breasts, prodding until you see stiff buds jutting out from the fabric of her dress. You can also see two tentacles creeping around her groin and butt area, going in and out as the mage grunts and gasps...
Stohohop stahaharing and hehehelp us! Ohohohoho, ahahahahaha!
Yehehehehes! And you reheheally ought not to look like youre ehehehehenjoying it sohoho muhuhuhuuch! Ahahahahahah! Gehehet awahahay!

Unfortunately (or maybe fortunately), Arthurs chastisements are derailed when you see some tentacles start creeping down his trousers too. You can only guess, but it seems likely his genitals are getting the amorous attentions of those stone tentacles too. From the bulge, hes gonna be rock-hard soon...
Think we can help them, bro?

You crane your neck and look up to where they are dangling in the air. Youd need to jump off something to reach them, and then what? If escape is impossible between Morgans magic and Arthurs muscles, what could you do with neither?
Dont think so. Ill see if we can deal with the Tickle Lords, but theres not much we can do right now, sorry.
Yeah, you should know were not exactly formidable. I promise you well come straight back the second we learn a stone-shattering spell though.

Youre not quite sure whats happening, at first. The female solider in the golden helmet and blue cape is surrounded by stone gargoyles, which have lifted her up arms and ripped off her steel grieves and high boots. Their stubby stone hands dont seem be scribbling or poking or anything like that, and they are simply holding them still, yet the soldier is squawking with high-pitched laughter all the same.
Ah, ahahahahah, stohohop! Ahahahaha! Tickles sohoho much!

Its then that the Tickle Lords words click into place. You lean in closer and see that the hands of the gargoyles are vibrating in place. Its the kind of movement you yourself could replicate, but perhaps only for a few seconds at a time and not nearly as quickly. You can see the gargoyles have placed these humming hands in strategic locations like the centres of the soles, armpits and between her legs, to potent, devastating effect. From the way the adventurer is sweating, you assume shes been here a while and probably been teased and denied for a while too, based on how you notice her laughter is punctuated with breathy groans and moans in between squawks of laughter.
Hmmm, Gargoyle Two, more vibrations on her armpits. Gargoyle One, move down and inch, and keep her feet steady. Gargoyle Three reduce the thrum, keep her on the edge.
Grahahaha, you mohohohonster! You cohohoward! Fahahace me in battle, not like th-th-thihihihis!

The Tickle Lord himself does not respond to the taunts, does not even dignify them with a response. He just watches. You find it a little odd that he does not partake in the tickling, simply standing still with his arms crossed and his face impassive. You see indifference, amusement, concentration, and ennui take turns flickering across his sharp grey features. He reminds you a little of a robot, a machine of cruel efficiency, stolid responsibility, and rigid duty. This is a man who will do his job  no less, and maybe more. And not a man you want to fight right now...

When your head stops spinning, you find yourself in a most curious predicament indeed. Burly angel and snarling demon statues have you three pinned down  you, Cissy, and Tickle Lord Matilda. There are no stocks or bondage here aside from their stone hands, but perhaps with their weight and implacable grip, thats enough, as they push down your ankles and wrists. Brock tsks over the three of you, shaking his head.
Uh, greetings, Brocks! It seems you have me in a rather exposed situation. Care to explain whats the meaning of this? I know Ive misinterpreted signals in the past...
He sighs and speaks in a low gravelly voice.
Youre here to proclaim your love? Return her affections?
Youre here to ravish her? Seduce and tickle her?
Hmmm, those sound pretty good to me...
No, and dont encourage her wild fantasies.
Ah, but what is this world if not a wild fantasy?
A dull dark one where jobs need to be done, quotas need to be reached, and responsibilities need to be accepted. I take no particular pleasure in this, Matilda, but I think you need a firm lesson.

No pleasure at all? Not even a little? Come on, don't you wanna tickle me good, get me all giggly, and have me fall into your arms? Come on, Brock! I've seen the way you look at me sometimes! Seen the way you look at my feet when you think I'm not looking...
So much lust... so very much.

His eyes follow yours and linger on Matildas bare feet. It seems youre about to be tickled, but at least you finally get a proper look at Matildas bare feet, though your position of being restrained beside her means you dont get much of a view of her soles, just the tops and toes. Maybe its the angle, but her feet seem very small and petite, with chipped toenail polish done a cheerful red. The painted digits wiggle about with a nervous energy. Juxtaposed besides Cissys similarly small pair, you observe the Tickle Lords feet are a little smaller, but thinner instead of chubby. They also have that same pale orange skin tone that indicated Matilda is not quite human, though the wings and ears are also giveaways. Tickle Lord Brock stops for a moment, blinks, and then shakes his head.
